channel.title: Smal G-zip issue
channel.description: When i go to "open with" on my .dat formatted models these days, i browse my computer for gzip to add it to the list, since it was deleted form it for some reason, it doesnt add it. So i cant get my models G-Zipped anymore to correct my cache.

item.title: Smal G-zip issue
item.dc:creator: @badger41 badger41
item.description:
@badger41 wrote:

[quote=“CoonHunter, post:8, topic:291991”][quote author=badger41 link=topic=385820.msg2892984#msg2892984 date=1249014068]

find your gzip file and just drag the modle onto gzip and it zips it or somthing

Thanks that worked, it used to work the old way i had it but idk what happened. I was acually getting ready to re-do my entire computer for the 3rd time this year.

thats dumb, if your going to write a virus you also need to write the thing that gets rid of it, considering you write 1 you should know where its going to install itself and know what it looks like…

maybe if you didnt look at so much porn you wouldnt have to re format so much
jk, try to re instal gzip and see if you can use the open with method again, but you could just drag the file onto it, im just saying
[/quote]
No actually i was testing a new virus i wrote and i didn’t realize my friends firewall sends back un-wanted information. So it came back after me and ate a bunch of my Windows files. The first time it didn’t go away, so i had that for about 2 months before i did it again. After that i finally went away. Also, whats the use of porn? Gives nothing but your hand. To me thats not worth it.[/quote]
